# ===================================================================
# This .gitignore is specifically for the contxt.news project
# Tech Stack: Vite, React, TypeScript, Webstorm, Node.js
# ===================================================================

# Dependencies
# This is the most important rule. The node_modules folder can contain
# thousands of files and is recreated by running `npm install`.
/node_modules

# Build output
# The /dist folder is generated by running `npm run build`. We only
# want to track our source code, not the compiled output.
/dist
/build
/.vite

# Logs
# Log files can be large and are specific to a single run.
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# Environment variables
# This is critical for security. Never commit .env files as they may
# contain secret API keys in the future.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# IDE configuration
# Ignores settings files generated by Webstorm and other common editors.
.idea/
.vscode/
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.swp

# Operating System files
# Ignores system-specific files that have no place in a shared repo.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# TypeScript cache files
*.tsbuildinfo
